text:
meet the girls behind the blog! 
survivor and mother of two dog-ters. as as a self taught artist, deloné did not pick up a paintbrush until 2009. it was trauma that pushed her creative outlet and in it, she found healing. she found a voice. among many other struggles, growing up bi-racial and searching for her identity has led her to embrace of human skin in her work. most of her subject matter comes from a place of dealing with her identity, childhood trauma, sexual abuse, and surviving an abusive relationship later in life. however, she wants people to see their own pain and healing through her work. she is a firm believer in cultivating healthy habits to deal with trauma and wants to help others do the same. yes, this road has been hard but she is thankful for the seasons and people who got her here. even the “mistakes.” the main thing she wants people to take away is you are not alone, it does get better, and there is a way to find gratitude even when it seems as though everything is crumbling around you. 
#donteatcandy

text:
tina tchen, roberta kaplan, hilary rosen, and fatima goss graves make up the time’s up legal defense fund. established in the wake of the harvey weinstein sexual abuse allegations, the fund connects victims of workplace sexual harassment with lawyers, then helps pay legal bills with donations from 50 states and 80 countries that have swelled to $22 million from $13 million. 
the #metoo legal guardians are on our #bloomberg50 list this year. tap to link in bio to read our interview with them. 
photograph by jeff brown for bloomberg businessweek

text:
power tables are made of white men and women
.

i think this is michelle obama's form of "#nameyourracist, which was *the* most amazing "game" on social media ever. there are too many for her to mention so she just said, "everyone in american 'power', ever. all at once"
.

and i'd like to do something rare (syke!) and compare this to my journey post book rejection! because i immediately stepped down, asking for explanations on weak (i said "sucky") parts, and bc there were any (yes there were but to quote mrs. obama, "they're just not smart" and missed them), so i got one line: "you spoke about the drawbacks of american health care" ...when i hve the approval in writing. not smart
.

literally? there is no "top", it's all just white people jacking off to monitory struggle, like the health care gap
.

and i think that was the real reason my ex-husband was pushed over the edge -- and i mean it; i'm not being ironic here. he expected something "behind the curtain-ish" and bc there isn't anything he couldn't properly reconcile his intellect against his fixed poverty. im mean, he was a janitor, but very much a genius. he thought he would find something that could match his elegance, but there really wasn't anything but more lazy ass terrorist white people
.

he cussed my mother out about it, which wasn't fair but i feel him. she has the kind of racialized blindness that is so subtle its caught in the air, and it will choke the shit out you the more you breath it in
.

and it was about tesla. he loves tesla and she was being dismissive and he just got at her. to everyone else at the table it was "liza, i'm not going to tell you to get a divorce, but that was not normal" but to me i was like "#twinning!" .

life is weird the closer you get to the top. you realize that all the "top" is made from is more money, which is the hight of manipulation, bc money is the weakest global currancy. like *all white people* (except anderson cooper) are the first victims of horizontal mobility. like, the same tired ass psychology, just now as "president"
.

america is incredibly unimpressive, which is why i just say whatever i please when *forced* to deal with the people behind it
.

text:
had a beautiful screening in santa monica. over 70 students showed up to see the film from all different backgrounds.

we had a powerful q and a after the film talking about how to combat trafficking, lgbtq rights, women's rights, assault, trauma, the filmmaking progress, how to be a mentor to youth, and actions to take right away to combat child trafficking. 
california's forgotten children documentary gives audiences a valuable understanding of commercial sexual exploitation through the voices of survivors and advocates in the movement. it is a proud feeling walking out of a screening knowing that the film inspired some people on their own journeys to create change in the world.

here is a picture of director melody miller, and faculty marla leech and sharyn obsatz from the journalism and film studies department at santa monica college. 
thank you for sharing the film at your school. looking forward to more collaborations in the future! ❤️ .
.

.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
#sisters #omgoddess my ma degree is part #anthropology so  #womenwhorunwiththewolves  book was  included 4 good luck in a pile of #books on the film set of my #metoo fempowered™ movie (2019) i'm now  #reading it !  validation 4 #authentic #handmade #findmytribe 🍃truliindie™🍃 #wild #wildcrafted
#cultures not bought$  like stocks "we consume culture same way we consume food - becoming it " (© excerpt from cali lili's declaration of indiependance ™ ) not all "indies" are created equal 
join calililiindies™ movement : #supporttheartsustaintheartist™ 
indie artists are navigating a marketplace in which rich corporations claim the word " indie " in order 2 capitalize on it's connotations
we are asking audiences 2 : 
#readthelabel on the "indie" movie or music you consume 
just as the same as one might " read the label " on a food item 
please consider asking questions about the #origins + "manufacture" of that so-called "indie " - just as you might do with #fruit #vegetables #coffee chocolate wine - fabrics etc. how was it made ? 
who made it? 
was it made by makers craftspersons ? 
or corporate deal-makers? 
do the proceeds go to the maker and support the maker's future endeavors or just support a middle-man corporation ? 
please consider finding out how to :  best support the work
all too easy to relegate the #noncorporate #diy artist + art to an irrelevant corner of our societies - pretending that what we do is not work - truth is - "artist rights" are indeed 'human rights.'
the way artists are treated in any society, is a direct reflection of the 'humanity' ( or inhumanity ) at the very foundations of civilization . 
history and #herstory show that cultures which elevate wealth and forms of "feudalism" / corporate greed - are simply depriving and ultimately dooming themselves to lack-luster, soulless futures on every level, including economic failure ... while #civilizations who encourage and support the thriving, not just surviving of their citizens who are living artists, are healthy nourished - balanced and whole on every level - including a respect for #wildlife #nature #ecological systems as well as human needs such as healthcare #education #socialjustice

text:
"violence often comes from our immediate surroundings and not from outside. i will keep an eye out for my environment and refuse to live with my eyes closed.” "i was running in a safe, well-lit, busy neighbourhood. i had a very clear idea of what is safe and what is dangerous. i didn’t make a mistake but the assault still happened." victoria makai, a hungarian ultramarathon runner, was sexually assaulted in a brutal way while on her run. after being released from the hospital, the mother of two refused to hide her wounds and decided to launch an anti-violence campaign “run away”.
"we hope to generate thought-provoking ideas that can help us increase our safety. we would welcome any action to advance this important cause. perhaps these campaign messages will help others to tell their own stories or draw the strength needed to make a change.” viktória said.

from 2014 to 2017, stone was president of the #malalafund, where she worked to empower girls globally.

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
महिलाओं के हक की आवाज उठाएंगी करीना खान

अगर आरजे बेहतरीन हो तो शो में आने वाले गेस्ट्स से उनके दिल के राज उगलवाना उसके बाएं हाथ का खेल होता है। तो अब बॉलीवुड की फीमेल सेलेब्स के दिल के राज उगलवाने के लिए आ रही है। एक खास रेडियो जॉकी, जी हां करीना कपूर अपने शो ‘वॉट वूमन वॉन्ट विद करीना कपूर खान’ (what women want with kareena kapoor khan) के साथ रेडियो के जरिए महिलाओं के हक की आवाज आपके घर तक लाने वाली हैं। वह हमेशा अपनी जॉली प्रकृति और बुलबुले अभिनय के साथ दर्शकों को चकित करती है, अब वह समय है जब वह अपनी आवाज़ से लोगों को खुश करेगी खबरों की पुष्टि करते हुए, करीना कपूर ने कहा कि वह लोगों के लिए अपना पहला शो सुनने के लिए और इंतजार नहीं कर  सकती है। #bollywood #follow #likeforlikes #love #india #hollywood #fashion #art #instagram #actor #mumbai #dubai #bhfyp #madhuridixit  #saraalikhan #kareenakapoor #womenpower  #girl #girls #girlspower #metoo #metoo #metoomovement #women #womenempowerment #womensfashion #womenanwser

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
since the age of 14, jayme’s life has been hell and she has one person to thank for it, pastor james madison.
:
he stood in the pulpit on sundays waving the same hands that abused her at night. he glorified god with the same mouth he used to chip away her self-esteem, daily. he was a man of god who had turned her away from the same god he told people they needed to serve.
:
he was the man who was supposed to pray for, take care of and eventually love her. instead he preyed on, took advantage of and shattered her heart before it had a chance to truly love someone else.
:
now, 14 years and a son later, she finds herself needing god yet she doesn’t know how to reach him. she longs for god but isn’t sure he can hear a sinner’s prayer until she starts to pray, dear god...

text:
❣️handpoked❣️ double dragon on my own thighs. 4 sessions. healed about 2-3 weeks.
.
.
tw: rape/abuse
i am a victim of violence and i’m not afraid to talk about it. healing is something that often shows little progress, until you look back from where you were and understand where you are now.

these dragons are my guardians. after years of rejecting myself, i’m finally able to be at peace with aspects of body that were once violated. every time i look down at my legs, i’m reminded of the love i’ve written on myself and my goals for loving myself in the future.

for me, tattooing is a way for me to heal and connect with my ancestry and myself. that is why i tattoo and why i choose to be tattooed. the process of tattooing is so important to me as a queer, transgender person of color. i want to share that healing with others, i want to share my story with others. because we are not alone in our own suffering. i want you to know that i’m here and i see you and that it’s okay.

thank you for supporting me, i will keep doing what i do.
.
.
.

text:
i am a person who doesn't believe in being a part of big groups. a person who is pretty much full of herself and don't feel the need to have a "social circle" to party on weekends. i have learnt the secret art of being content with my ownself, hence i usually avoid social gatherings until they are useful to me or my work.  my work makes me surrounded with hundreds of people everyday, i don't run away from that part but yes, i always find an escape from seasonal friendships and unreal presence of people.
•
the difference between these two facts about me is, a conserved person as i am, when it comes to giving a special pedestal in my life, that i call friendship; i value the commitment as i value the presence of parents in my life. that's why i can't losely call someone my friend. 
here, she is that one person who constantly reminds me that i'm not a psycho or grumpy adult who is always unhappy to see people around haha.
since college she has been my support system, be it motivating me for my abilities, boosting my confidence or just helping me out from "boy troubles" of life. she has been there. saved me from all the wrong decisions, also, became my partner in crime. my anchor to the uncontrolled ship which would have otherwise flown and crashed to the waves of uncertainties of ocean called life. 
she is restoring my faith in the word "friend" and trespassing my territories since a long time. she made me feel beautiful inside out. she restored my faith in friendship. ❤️ she's radhika @radhika8901 ❤
.
.
- by charu @ecstatic_being .
.
................................................................
.
.
in these times of #metoo and stories of sexual harassment, there are also women and men around us who made us feel more beautiful, more confident and powerful from both inside and out. 
if there is such a person in your life who ever made you feel so about yourself then wait no longer and share your story too. let us pay a small tribute to her/him here @shespeaksforthechange.

we all need such people around us afterall, don't we?
(dm us your story or tag us in your post.)

text:
❣️handpoked❣️ double dragon on my own thighs. 4 sessions. healed about 2-3 weeks. please follow @grelysian.tattoos for more of my tattooing.
.
.
tw: rape/abuse
i am a victim of violence and i’m not afraid to talk about it. healing is something that often shows little progress, until you look back from where you were and understand where you are now.

these dragons are my guardians. after years of rejecting myself, i’m finally able to be at peace with aspects of body that were once violated. every time i look down at my legs, i’m reminded of the love i’ve written on myself and my goals for loving myself in the future.

for me, tattooing is a way for me to heal and connect with my ancestry and myself. that is why i tattoo and why i choose to be tattooed. the process of tattooing is so important to me as a queer, transgender person of color. i want to share that healing with others, i want to share my story with others. because we are not alone in our own suffering. i want you to know that i’m here and i see you and that it’s okay.

thank you for supporting me, i will keep doing what i do.
.
.
.

text:
un cine foro fue organizado en san cristóbal, estado táchira, por el tribunal de violencia contra la mujer, como organismo miembro de la red de espacios seguros, en el marco de los 16 días de activismo contra la violencia de género.

la actividad fue realizada en coordinación con la agencia de las naciones unidas para los refugiados (acnur) en venezuela, y participaron varias organizaciones. entre ellas estuvieron ret, intamujer, spinna, la asociación civil mujeres empoderadas, funcionarios de la inspectoría general de tribunales y actores sociales involucrados en la defensa y atención de las víctimas de violencia.

la proyectada fue la película la cabaña. una vez finalizada la proyección del film, se ofreció un análisis a los presentes sobre el daño que puede ocasionar el maltrato físico y psicológico desde la infancia y se hizo un llamado a la no violencia.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
📷: ©acnur / tatiana font

text:
una caminata tuvo lugar en el estado apure, en el marco del día internacional de la eliminación de la violencia contra la mujer.

esta actividad, que forma parte del inicio de los 16 días de activismo, fue organizada por promotores comunitarios de puerto páez y contó con el apoyo de la agencia de las naciones unidas para los refugiados (acnur) en venezuela y la organización socia hias.

también estuvieron presentes estudiantes, docentes, personas en necesidad de protección internacional y población de acogida de personas refugiadas.

text:
la agencia de las naciones unidas para los refugiados (acnur) en venezuela, miembros de la red de espacios seguros del estado bolívar, ministerio público y policía municipal de caroní realizaron una jornada de información pública en el marco del día internacional de la eliminación de la violencia contra la mujer y los 16 días de activismo.

la actividad organizada bajo el lema "las mariposas toman el centro comercial orinokia" permitió dar a conocer la labor de la red de espacios seguros y efectuar, al mismo tiempo, distintas dinámicas para abordar temas como: vacunación contra la violencia de género, pintando el mundo de igualdad, rincón infantil y performance “ayer me mataron”.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
se efectuó un animado recorrido por el lugar y esto permitió entregar material informativo aproximadamente a 400 personas, sobre violencia de género, rutas de atención, servicios públicos y organizaciones presentes.

las mariposas fueron usadas como símbolo de la fuerza mostrada por las hermanas mirabal, fallecidas en tiempos de dictadura y quienes inspiraron la conmemoración de los 16 días de activismo en las américas.

text:
con una colorida actividad realizada en el parque metropolitano de la ciudad de san cristóbal se dió inicio a los 16 días de activismo contra la violencia de género.

este encuentro se realizó gracias al trabajo conjunto de la red de espacios seguros, conformada por acnur, hias, cisp, ret, consejo noruego para los refugiados, servicio jesuita de refugiados e intamujer. también contó con el apoyo de la alcaldía de san cristóbal y otras organizaciones gubernamentales.

desde tempranas horas fue iniciado el evento con una feria de medios de vida, donde participaron las niñas de la casa de abrigo corazones nuevos y solicitantes de la condición de refugiados. también refugiadas mostraron a los asistentes sus dotes gastronómicos.

en esta jornada recreativa se ofreció información sobre  la red de espacios seguros. además se desarrollaron actividades deportivas como zumba y salsa fit. al ritmo de la música y con mucho entusiasmo los presentes hicieron un llamado a la "no violencia". los niños y niñas presentes elaboraron carteles alrusivos a la prevención de la violencia de género.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
📷: ©acnur / tatiana font

text:
la agencia de las naciones unidas para los refugiados (acnur) en venezuela realizó el segundo curso para funcionarios de la policía migratoria del estado zulia. esta cohorte estuvo integrada por un total de cincuenta funcionarios.

la agenda de formación culminó con una capacitación sobre los derechos de la población lgbti. durante la actividad fueron abordados los aspectos de la sexualidad y diversidad sexual y se ofrecieron herramientas para el análisis y entrevistas de casos. estos encuentros buscan sensibilizar, fomentando el respeto y el trato digno  para las personas lgbti.

las clases tuvieron lugar en la sede de la universidad nacional experimental de la seguridad ubicada en el estado zulia. la comisión nacional para los refugiados (conare) y otras organizaciones socias como hias, ret, cruz roja y oim también participaron como facilitadores.

este tipo de cursos es parte de una iniciativa del acnur que busca el fortalecimiento de las labores de los integrantes de la policía migratoria.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
📷: ©acnur / tatiana font

text:
en el marco de los 16 días de activismo contra la violencia de género, la red de espacios seguros organizó un taller sobre salud sexual y reproductiva, y prevención contra la violencia en la comunidad mi pequeña barinas, ubicada en san antonio, estado táchira.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
finalizada la charla, y como parte de la actividad, las mujeres miembros del comité de violencia basada en género y los integrantes de la red de jóvenes de esa localidad elaboraron carteles con los diferentes tipos de violencia y luego replicaron a los asistentes el contenido aprendido.

creyones y libros para colorear fueron ofrecidos a los niños y niñas asistentes como parte de una actividad de integración.
⠀⠀⠀⠀
📷: ©acnur / tatiana font

text:
una “formación sobre salud sexual y reproductiva  y la violencia de género” fue realizada en el estado bolívar, en el marco del convenio de entendimiento entre la agencia de naciones unidas para los refugiados (acnur) en venezuela y el fondo de población de las naciones unidas (unfpa).
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
entre los participantes estuvieron la organización socia hias, fundación ret -protegiendo a través de la educación-, cruz roja seccional caroní, orgullo guayana, amnistía internacional, ateneo ecológico del orinoco, la comisión para los derechos humanos y la ciudadanía, la defensoría del pueblo y el ministerio público.

este tipo de actividades busca darle continuidad a las acciones conjuntas para el fortalecimiento de la red de espacios seguros del estado bolívar y respaldar el abordaje de temas relevantes para esta instancia, como la salud sexual y reproductiva, tomando en cuenta que el embarazo adolescente fue una de las problemáticas identificadas por las organizaciones activas en el entorno comunitario.

según el trabajo adelantado hasta el momento en las zonas identificadas como prioritarias por acnur, la población refugiada está compuesta en su mayoría de mujeres solas jefas de hogar, quienes en promedio tienen de tres a cuatro hijos y viven en zonas rurales, donde en muchas ocasiones los servicios de salud son escasos o inexistentes.

la formación incluyó un marco teórico sobre la “introducción al paquete de servicios iniciales mínimos (psim) para la salud reproductiva” y una explicación sobre la “integración de acciones en salud sexual y reproductiva y violencia basada en género”, dictadas por el doctor juan pablo protto, consultor regional de asuntos humanitarios del fondo de población de las naciones unidas, quien partiendo de su experiencia pudo ayudar a comprender a la audiencia por qué la salud sexual y reproductiva es parte integral del bienestar personal.

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text_retweet:
i think there is a real difference  between "no means no" and "yes means yes". the first tends to set a precedent for  consent to be assumed rather than confirmed. sometimes, the aggressor can choose to ignore body language or subtle rejections, and the recipient for whatever reason may not be able to verbalize their discomfort in the moment. in either case, if someone is incapacitated in any way, they cannot give legal consent to physicality. •
•
a "no" is definitely 💯💯💯a reason to stop, but without a "yes", it shouldn't be an automatic go! it is time that we all set a new standard for checking in with our partners. consent yesterday doesn't necessarily mean consent today; consent to first base does not imply a home run. if we ask the questions about desires and needs first, we have way less probability of dispute after the fact; this is how we build foundations for strong relationships. every physical interaction should always be a mutual understanding and reflection of respect, and silence or implication does not ever equal consent. get an answer before taking action. •
•

text: “we curled up on the love seat together, his arm around me, and we watched several episodes before his mom popped her head into the room and asked if we wanted dessert. she stood momentarily in the doorway before returning downstairs. a few minutes later, instead of his mom returning with our plates, noah’s dad came up. he walked into the room with a plate in each hand and stood there with the giddiest, most genuinely excited smile on his face. he remained like that for an uncomfortable amount of time before remembering to hand us our plates. once he finished his assignment, he stood back, smiling once again. he began to walk from the room but stopped just at the doorway until noah’s mom, who had been standing in the hallway, pulled him away. i leaned over closer to noah and whispered, “they think we’re cute.” “yep. they’ve been standing there for twenty minutes. i feel like i’m in middle school again,” noah softly replied, giving me a playful squeeze. we watched several more episodes, completing the first disk, until it was time for another crowther christmas tradition, which, for noah, was meeting up with his best friend dorian for a movie.” -r. macceile now - dec 25th 100% of proceeds from my books go entirely toward my #holiday #charity #fundraiser benefiting the #afsp you can find more info on rebeccasbookshop.com candy apple butterscotch: a memoir available now! #fourstars #memoir #metoo #ptsdsurvivor “it’s worth the read it’s about a #woman #empowered and my god that is a #wonderful thing indeed” #linkinbio #authorsofinstagram #independentpublishing #goodreads #newbookalert #readforfree

text:
a few months ago, amidst another jarring wave of national news, @kellywilt and i met to discuss our shared need to do something to help both ourselves and others who have experienced trauma. we wanted to create a space where people felt heard and seen, in a place where they would feel a sense of deep belonging, to heal. the soulshine retreat was born.
.
the soulshine retreat is a highly intentional weekend of healing in community. a place to safely share your story and soak up positivity and light. a haven in the mountains.
.
our vision is closer than ever to coming to life now. we will be hosting the first of two informational meetings at the ninth house tonight at 6 pm.
.
if you feel a call to join us, please see the link in our bio for lots more info, dm, or attend the meeting.
.
#healingincommunity #soulshine #sisterhood #bebrave #brenebrown #womensretreat #shareyourstory #believesurvivors #metoo #tucsonaz #womenempoweringwomen #theninthhouse

text:
👇😞
dear wrongdoer,
it was humiliating.
what was it entirely? i thought again.
i couldn't name it. i didn't have words.
maybe sexting or one sided love or humiliation.
then, i named it opprobrium.
misunderstanding was the word given to me for not loving someone.
i was screaming but silently.
i was in pain but still smiling to hide it.
it felt as if i was alone & dying.
thus, causing me to untrust everyone around.
and so i trusted - "he that is low, has no pride."
i came to poetry to lessen this.
but this was a kind of intolerable complicity.
-from an ill-matched person you loved.

@poetrybypriyanshi via @priyanshi.jain05
🖤

text: i’m a greatly empathetic yet sometimes difficult person. i hold in my feelings often wearing the face of “i’m fine” even when i’m falling apart inside. it has always worked in the past or seemed to. however, those who really know me can see through the barriers that i set around myself out of fear of loss, abandonment and vulnerability. i have recently embarked on a new journey aiming to cleanse myself of some dark memories and experiences from my past that i used the same method of repression to keep at bay. the nightmares and instances of rage are uncontrollable and i’m honestly lost. the support has been great and appreciated but the backlash even greater so the battle is uphill but in no way impossible. i am grateful for my journey and apologize in advance if i might say or do anything to offend or hurt anyone. 🔆 #metoo

text:
"many of us were raised to say yes. we're still learning how to say no, when so often our no goes unheard." in our boundaries issue, writer ilana masad discusses the importance of communication in relationships. "in recent months, the #metoo movement has exploded into prominence. with all its issues—its focus on white, wealthy, famous women, its early erasure of the originator of the hashtag, tarana burke—it has at least caused a larger swath of the population to talk about sexual harassment, assault, and the role of power. but something we don't talk about nearly often enough is how communication sits squarely in these dynamics as well." get the full story in anxy no. 3, available via link in bio. illustration by @nalghadban

text: get your tickets now before they sell out! link in bio. this is my story, my true life that i’ve put into words, characters, and multi media. it’s a 60 minute one woman show about my breast cancer journey. it’s funny, heart breaking, & joyful. yes, there is so much in a cancer patients journey including joy & love & kindness. see the ups & downs, the trauma, the new normal identity seeking, the anger, the hurt that encompasses a life changing event. one of my most exciting experiences with this show was this summer in the edinburgh fringe festival. there were 3,998 shows in fringe & mine was listed as one of the top 10 body positive shows to see @edfringe! in this day & age when women fight for truth, being heard, female love, equality, this was truly wonderful. come on by friday january 18th, 2019 at 8pm , @whitefiretheatre . #chemobarbie #artheals #love #kindness #womenempowerment #solofest2019 #metoo #breastcancer #fertility #youngsurvivor #cancercare #breasties #bca #soloshow #lathtr #losangeles #comedy #drama #pain #betrayal #bullying #peace #pink #triplepositive #socialmedia #positive

text:
#withtou #metoo #school_metoo #스쿨미투 #정신여고 #정신여고공론화 @cs_schoolmetoo
용기 있는 후배님들의 스쿨미투를 응원합니다.

우리 모교도 미투가 터질줄 알았지!
긍지높은 기독교 학교면 뭐합니까
학교 전통이 뼈대 깊은 만큼
피해자가 매년 속출 하는데... 학생들이 그 안에서 성희롱,성추행 당하는데
아직도 딸 같아서 농담이랍시고 그러십니까?
우리 학교 출신 교생, 교사분들도 많은데
눈가리고 아웅 하신 모교출신 교직원 분들,
교장,교감,목사,부목사 전부 다 책임있습니다.

그리고 제발 문제 있는 교사 해임시키세요.
오죽하면 학생들이 공론화 했겠습니까
학교만큼 학생들도 타격 받습니다.

물론 좋은 교사분들 많이 계시고
저도 즐겁게 학창시절 보냈지만
성희롱, 성추행은 계속 있었습니다.
단지 대학을 갈 때 불이익을 볼까봐
교실에 돌아와 상처입고 울거나 쌍욕하면서 친구들과 얘기하며 덮었을 뿐입니다.

그리고 학생 뿐 아니라 교생 실습하는 분들께도 충분히 성희롱 하던 교사 있었고 피해자가 적지 않을겁니다.

아직도 사실무근이다, 근거없다,
사과하고 넘어간 부분이다 이렇게 하실건가요?
교사분들 어디가서 긍지높은 기독교 학교라고
자랑스러워 마세요 부끄러워 죽겠으니까요.
name: Sujin Lee

text:
a student from the missouri state university (msu) has been charged for allegedly raping a woman hours after she attended a #metoo rally in springfield over the weekend. according to a report by the , zachary alperin, 22, went to some bars with the victim after the rally ended, and then went to the woman’s room on campus, per the court documents.
in her statement, the victim said that she allowed zachary to sleep in her room but told him not to touch her because she was drunk, the springfield news-leader reported. the woman told police that she fell asleep and woke up to find alperin lying naked on top of her. per the springfield news-leader, the woman “alleged that alperin performed sex acts on her and she pushed him away.”
alperin allegedly confessed to performing sexual acts on the victim, as reported by the springfield news-leader. “i guess i tried to force myself on her, and i feel like such a terrible person for it,” the culprit told police. alperin is currently being held at the greene county jail on a bond of $20,000 following the investigation. he has been charged with second-degree rape and second-degree sodomy.
according to state law, if someone is convicted of rape and sodomy in the second degree, they can incur a maximum imprisonment of seven years, along with fines up to $10,000 for each offence. following the news, organizers of the #metoo rally in springfield expressed their shock at the incident and said that they have been “devastated” by the news. however, they appreciated that the victim mustered the courage to report the rape, a report by said.
“we are devastated. the thought that someone would leave our rally feeling so encouraged, just to be raped a few hours later… it is almost too much,” the organizers wrote in a facebook post, as quoted by nbc news. “if the woman who attended our rally that the article is referring to sees this, please know this: we are so proud of you for your bravery in coming forward. we are so sorry. we believe you. this was not your fault in any way. we are here for you,” it further read.

text:
el 8 de diciembre de 1984 se suicida en mar del plata la tenista mary terán de weiss “si a evita no le perdonaban ser mujer, conmigo no iban a ser menos”

primera argentina en alcanzar los primeros planos del tenis mundial, mary terán disputó 1.100 encuentros internacionales de los que triunfó en 832, imponiéndose en los torneos abierto de irlanda (1950), israel (1950), colonia (alemania) (1951), baden-baden (1951) y welsh (1954), y obtuvo varias veces el torneo del río de la plata. ganó dos medallas de oro (single y doble femenino con felisa piérola) y una de bronce (dobles mixto con alejo rusell) en los primeros juegos deportivos panamericanos disputados en buenos aires en 1951, siendo una de las grandes figuras de este torneo. en esta época fue considerada una de las mejores 20 tenistas del mundo.  simpatizante peronista, a partir de la dictadura de la "revolución libertadora" fue perseguida por sus ideas políticas, se le prohibió toda participación deportiva en el país y debió refugiarse en el extranjero.

osvaldo jara en los malditos dice :
mientras debe permanecer en el viejo continente, forzosamente, en bs as confiscan sus bienes. con ayuda del general perón consigue la ciudadanía española y representa a este país. la prensa argentina no dedica una sola línea a los logros. 
en agosto de 1959 regresa al país. las condiciones ya eran otras y si bien logra recuperar sus bienes expropiados, hubo quienes hicieron todo lo posible por seguir condenándola al ostracismo. quiso jugar tenis representando el belgrano athletic, y los directivos de dicha institución no se lo permitieron. esta actitud de marginamiento se haría extensiva “quise asociarme a los clubes belgrano social y gimnasia y esgrima de buenos aires –relataría mary-, negándos

text:
@helsinginsanomat @helsinginratsupoliisi @nyt.fi @nytimestravel @nytimesfashion @mynytimes @nytimes wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
@helsinginsanomat @helsinkipoliisi @nyt.fi @nytimestravel @nytimesfashion @mynytimes @nytimes 
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green, author
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

i need the breastplate of righteousness to protect my heart.

•

•

text:
it was late last night - we were already in bed - when we got the message that a friend of jarens passed away.
.
i did not know this individual so whole he sat and watched a video of this mans life i laid next to him.
.
as pictures of this man and his family filled jarens screen i listened to the instrumental music play and the rain that was tapping softly against our windows and i thought about my own family.
.
it was one of those spiritual moments when life seems to slow down and everything that you thought mattered no longer seems relevant and you get a glimpse into how much god loves you, how much he loves your family. how much you love your family! and you know right then that they are what is important. you’ve always known that of course, but in this moment you feel it!
.
so hold your loved ones today (including your teenagers who act like they don’t want it) because families are pretty awesome, aren’t they?!?! i am so very grateful for mine and each and every day i get to spend with them! ♥️

text_retweet:
#repost @onubrasil
.
artigo: salvemos a vida das mulheres na américa latina — uma mudança de mentalidade (por izumi nakamitsu, representante das @nacoesunidas para assuntos de desarmamento)
•
a igualdade entre homens e mulheres continua sendo um assunto pendente. o movimento #metoo colocou a atenção internacional na prevalência generalizada da agressão sexual e do assédio.

a verdade é que a violência contra mulheres e meninas é uma das violações de direitos humanos mais comuns, arraigadas e devastadoras do mundo.

em muitos lugares, essa violência é parte da vida cotidiana, é uma ameaça constante apoiada em noções destrutivas de masculinidade e que dá forma às interações humanas.

o machismo está presente na vida cotidiana da américa latina, apesar de não ser exclusivo dessa região. esta noção arcaica de masculinidade, em conjunto com a ampla disponibilidade de armas de fogo, é uma receita para aqueles que se sentem no direito de exercer poder sobre outros.

nos lares e entre parceiros, o poder das armas para ameaçar e aterrorizar faz com que atos como assédio e estupro sejam fáceis de serem cometidos pelos abusadores. os perpetuadores atacam cotidianamente indivíduos por meses e anos, e seus crimes só são interrompidos com a morte de suas vítimas.

a américa latina abriga 14 dos 25 países onde o feminicídio é mais comum. doze assassinatos motivados por gênero ocorrem na região a cada dia, a maioria por meio de armas de fogo, e as leis não garantem justiça para 49 de cada 50 vítimas. •
nos últimos anos, foi firmada uma série de compromissos internacionais para combater a violência de gênero. mencionarei três deles. (continua nos comentários)

nos lares e entre parceiros, o poder das armas para ameaçar e aterrorizar faz com que atos como assédio e estupro sejam fáceis de serem cometidos pelos abusadores. os perpetuadores atacam cotidianamente indivíduos por meses e anos, e seus crimes só são interrompidos com a moe de suas vítimas.

a américa latina abriga 14 dos 25 países onde o feminicídio é mais comum. doze assassinatos motivados por gênero ocorrem na região a cada dia, a maioria por meio de armas de fogo, e as leis não garantem justiça para 49 de cada 50 vítimas. •
nos últimos anos, foi firmada uma série de compromissos internacionais para combater a violência de gênero. mencionarei três deles. (continua nos comentários)

text:
"gender based violence (gbv) is a global health, human rights and development issue that transcends geography, class, culture, age, race and religion to affect every community and country in every corner of the world. the article 1 of un declaration on the elimination of violence 1993 provides a definition of gender - based abuse, calling it "any act of gender - based violence that results in, or is likely to result in, physical, sexual or psychological harm or suffering to women, including threats of such acts, coercion or arbitrary deprivation of liberty, whether occurring in public or in private life”. in india, gender based violence has many manifestations; from the more universally prevalent forms of domestic and sexual violence including rape, to harmful practices such as, dowry, honour killings, acid attacks, witch - hunting, sexual harassment, child sexual abuse, trafficking for commercial sexual exploitation, child marriage, sex selective abortion, sati etc.
.
ministry of women and child development, has formulated a centrally sponsored scheme for setting up one stop centre, a sub-scheme of umbrella scheme for national mission for empowerment of women including indira gandhi mattritav sahyaog yojana. popularly known as sakhi, the scheme is being implemented since 1st april 2015. these centres are being established across the country to provide integrated support and assistance under one roof to women affected by violence, both in private and public spaces in phased manner." .
#aashaishere
.
we have made it our mission to pay special attention to the needs and requirements of the survivors of sexual assault and violence in our country. we offer products that caters to the basic necessities of survivors of assault such as the aasha dna evidence sample collection (mo) kits for victims of sexual assualt which is of a high quality and is free of cost to the survivor. .
.
.

text_retweet:
#repost @ann.lew.is with @get_repost
・・・
one in five of us
•
on display thru tomorrow evening at @pulseartfair •
when i explain to people that it represents the real life statistic that 20% of american women will be raped in their lifetimes i’m met with grimaces, gulps, and nervous darting eyes. people get quiet and don’t ask questions. this number is too big for us to be unable to speak freely about the atrocity of rape. i’m finding through these tough conversations that we as a culture don’t have the language to speak about these violations of our bodies- a fundamental element if we are to change things. we’re scared to discuss it, it’s triggering, it’s so delicate, it’s unsafe, it creates vulnerability in all parties of the conversation. 
we have to be willing to have uncomfortable conversations if things are going to change. i know miami isn’t usually the place to have this moments but without our presence in these spaces we will continue to only scratch the surface. 
we must be willing to unearth these monstrous problems and deal with them directly instead of allowing them to stay buried, festering, rotting, and infecting us all. 
we must be brave. we must work to dismantle the patriarchal silence that blankets sexual violence against all people. silence is what holds us down. silence is the bedfellow of oppression. •
#annlewis #oneinfiveofus #pulsemiamibeach18 #rape #activistart #installationart #womensrights #rapeculture #america #equality #metoo #timesup

victoria’s secret has clung to the idea that women should look sexy for men. and while it is still the leading lingerie brand in the u.s., the company must compete with a handful of brands founded by women, for women. the lingerie brand’s stock is down 41 percent this year and the ratings from their annual fashion show — which aired on abc on sunday — hit a record low, according to the @hollywoodreporter. last month, the ceo jan singer resigned over comments made by the cmo, who declared the company had “no interest” in featuring plus-size or trans models because victoria’s secret “is about fantasy.” is it any wonder the brand is struggling in a #metoo era? 📸: béatrice de géa

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
steel
how does one find one’s steel?
one has to forge it! 
if one understands that we are ultimately always in a raw state…. like a newborn!  we can start anew at any given moment.….. we can begin to eliminate our impurities…… our negative thoughts and emotions…. our bad habits…. and become aware of the narratives we play and replay in our minds. similar to the process of steel making we must take on  high heat (challenges and seemingly impossible tasks) and embrace adversity. we must take these on willingly. that is where we begin to forge our steel. the very high heat….. repeated action of pounding, grinding and sharpening. this repeated action…… daily……. is what one needs. 
this is hard! 
it’s hard work….. relentless work and brutal honesty with oneself. 
one knows when one is ready. it’s a whisper at first……and then the whisper gets louder and can no longer be ignored. we can’t silence that constant chatter in our mind! thats when one asks…… ‘ why am i feeling this…… dissatisfaction?’
that is the time to begin the search for the true meaning and purpose of one’s existence. that process is finding ( forging ) your steel.
•asl notebooks, 2008 @asleninde

if one understands that we are ultimately always in a raw state…. like a newborn!  we can start anew at any given moment.….. we can begin to eliminate our impurities…… our negative thoughts and emotions…. our bad habits…. and become aware of the narratives we play and replay in our minds. similar to the process of steel making we must take on  high heat (challenges and seemingly impossible tasks) and embrace adversity. we must take these on willingly. that is where we begin to forge our steel. the very high heat….. repeated action of pounding, grinding and sharpening. this repeated action…… daily……. is what one needs. 
this is hard! 
it’s hard work….. relentless work and brutal honesty with oneself. 
one knows when one is ready. it’s a whisper at first……and then the whisper gets louder and can no longer be ignored. we can’t silence that constant chatter in our mind! thats when one asks…… ‘ why am i feeling this…… dissatisfaction?’
that is the time to begin the search for the true meaning and purpose of one’s existence. that process is finding ( forging ) your steel.
•asl notebooks, 2008 @asleninde

.
the ones who do.. are the ones who make the greatest impact. .
.
because once you turn your pain into power.. you become unstoppable. a warrior not a victim.
.
.
and nothing will break you.

text:
http://courtroomwatch.org/2018/12/05/medically-kidnapped-christian-activist-professor-solange-martinez-at-nyc-bronx-central-hospital/

life sentence for medically kidnapped christian activist professor solange martinez at nyc bronx central hospital
december 5, 2018 daniel j leach jr 
please help save medically kidnapped christian activist professor solange martinez who got life sentence in psychiatric hospital with forced.medication.
solange martinez is being held at north central hospital in the bronx . she  has been advocating for the poor and has been successfull in helping people in the court system . she has had several victories against the nyc social services agencies when they committed fraud . she is not an attorney and for that reason the legal system feels threatened by her . if everyone started representing themselves and others , it would take away billions of dollars from  the attorneys , judges , police , courts , prisons , transport companies , hospitals , doctors , nurses , social workers , certified public accountants , maintence workers , food service providers , cleaning services , security agents , internet providers , computer technicians , and all their supporting staff , buisness and corporations . so they locked her up . they are trying to silence her with a 60 year sentence and forced medication which has already begun . the drugs include : halidol , zolpidan , lithium carbonate and others . she is already getting tired and dizzy . a witness to her abduction heard officers of the nypd from precinct 52 say : 'we have determined that no crime has been committed here , the emt's are going to take you.' the emt stated : 'you can sue us later' . witnesses heard the chief of security at jacoby hospital , where the hearing was held , make the following statement : 'you are not here because you are mentally ill . you are here because you think your so smart .' also please help by calling the rutherford institute on solange martinez’s behalf.

the rutherford institute
post office box 7482
charlottesville, va 22906-7482

phone: (434) 978-3888 (8:30 am – 5:00 pm est) #
fax: (434) 978-1789
email: staff@rutherford.org

text:
sexism, this word is still viewed as a “bad” word. how dare i point out the reality that still remains alive and well in 2018!! first, let’s define sexism: a type of discrimination that undervalues, belittles, and treats a certain gender, often women, differently from the opposite gender. sexism may be conscious or unconscious, intentional or unintentional, and can impact people’s work.  we are expected to stay docile and polite and respond affirmatively regardless of the circumstances. this my friends is sexism!  in order to eradicate this behavior we must stand united. standing idly by watching another female stand alone in her attempt to correct inequality will only extend our anti-discrimination efforts. the effect of, “every women for her self” mentality is disastrous for our path to equality.  imagine for a moment, a world where all women support each other.  i, for one, refuse to ignore the challenges and double standards we face.
“each time a woman stands up for herself, without knowing it possibly, without claiming it, she stands up for all women.” ~ maya angelou

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
89년 10월호 주부생활에 실린 권인숙씨의 기사. 80년대에 자신의 성고문 사실을 고백하며 군사정권의 인권유린에 경종을 울린 미투 사건의 주인공인 권인숙씨이다.
저 기사에는 결혼기사만 실렸지만,  그녀는 95년에 결국 이혼하고 만다. 남편과 시댁과의 갈등이 불거질때마다 성고문 사건을 들먹이며 인격모욕을 하는걸 참을수 없었다고 한다.불쌍한것 거둬줬다는 식으로 취급을 했다고 한다. 자세한 사연은 그녀의 자서전 '선택'에 있다고 한다
그리고 위자료와 재산분할 한푼 못받고 이혼하고, 딸과 함께 미국유학을 가서 박사 학위 취득을 하시고 지금은 교수님으로 활동중이시다
과거는 누구에게나 있는것이고, 과거는 과거일뿐 아닐까?과거가 있다는 것보다 용서하는건 미래와 비전이 없다는 것인데.
상대를 고를땐 과거보다 미래의 비전을 보는 분을 만나셨다면 좋았을것이고 언론이 너무 사생활을 안 들췄다면 조용히 잘 살수 있지 않았을까 싶다.
지금 행복하게 잘 지내시면 좋겠다

text:
фредова
⠀
один из моих любимых сериалов - "рассказ служанки". такой, знаете, пробирающий до костей ужас и неверие: "ну, у нас такого-то точно не может быть".
⠀
казалось бы.
⠀
но гуляя по просторам русского инстаграма, в который раз убеждаешься, на постсовке женщина без "мужского плеча" (а лучше руки, которая "ненавязчиво" жамкает ее круглые ягодицы) в профиле - не выжить.
⠀
конец 2018 года, прогремевший #metoo, сексуальные домогательства,  как любят утверждать олеги "эпоха победившего феминизма", но инстаграм дивы продолжают ставить в ники имена мужиков: "такая-то такого-то".
⠀
серьезно?
⠀
чего тебя бомбит-то маша, хочется мне спросить саму себя. но я знаю ответ.
⠀
потому что это - самая настоящая антиутопия. чем отличается "фредова" от "оксаны_олега"? чем отличается красный плащ от "он тебе разрешает фоткаться в трусах?/олег хочет, чтобы я вставила импланты/покрасилась в блондинку"?
⠀
неужели это не очевидно, что выстраивать империю на том, что ты раскрыла секрет счастливого олега - равноценно набитой на заду татуировке с его именем и розами вокруг?
⠀
нет ничего плохого в счастливых отношениях и нет, это я не от зависти говорю.
⠀
но счастливые отношения - это союз двух или более зрелых, цельных людей, которые знают, что они из себя представляют по отдельности, не только в симбиозе.
⠀
а история о том, как построить идиллию с олегом - это рассказ служанки. даже если вам в этой серии и не оторвали палец.
⠀
любите советы о счастливой семейной жизни из рассказа служанки?
⠀
#еврейскийфеминизм

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
#violenciadegenero 
#segundavuelta #referendum

este 9 de diciembre se realizará la segunda vuelta en 15 regiones del país a fin de elegir a gobernadores y vicegobernadores; y al mismo tiempo los peruanos participaremos en el referéndum 2018 sobre cuatro reformas constitucionales.

en el caso de arequipa, la coyuntura social y política de los últimos días ha desencadenado distintos enfrentamientos entre los postulantes al gobierno regional.
y si bien nos encontramos a puertas de dichas elecciones, es importante señalar que existe un gran desazón en cuanto al tema de la violencia planteado en los planes de gobierno por los distintos candidatos, puesto que no han podido aclarar el panorama de cómo es que se manejará dentro de los cuatro próximos años ni tampoco han podido convencer a una gran mayoria de colectivos, movimientos y asociaciones que luchan contra la violencia, los cuales nos hemos unido para presentar el siguiente video.

recordemos la importancia de elegir no sólo a un buen administrador de nuestros recursos, sino, a una persona que merezca el reconocimiento como líder y que esto sea basado en una conducta adecuada, sin señalamientos que percudan su imagen y que lidere no solamente en lo ejecutivo, sino también en un comportamiento que sea meritorio a un líder y gobernante de una región tan importante como la nuestra
la calidad de la personas se demuestra en sus actos, y estos son un termómetro y un aviso de lo que nos puede o no convenir.

agradecimiento: 
deseamos agradecer al señor pedro roger acosta escobar por su colaboración en la realización del presente video.

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking in 2014, steve bannon – then executive chairman of the “alt-right” news network breitbart – was christopher wylie’s boss. and robert mercer, the secretive us hedge-fund billionaire and republican donor, was cambridge analytica’s investor. and the idea they bought into was to bring big data and social media to an established military methodology – “information operations” – then turn it on the us electorate.

cambridge analytica’s parent company, scl, had won contracts with the us state department and was pitching to the pentagon, and wylie was genuinely freaked out. - it’s insane, he told me one night. - the company has created psychological profiles of 230 million americans. and now they want to work with the pentagon? it’s like nixon on steroids.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking - bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking - bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

msyd-asra mamak toplum  merkezi’nde kadına ve kız çocuklarına yönelik şiddete karşı farkındalık aktivitileri devam ediyor.
mamak toplum merkezi’ndeki faydalanıcılarımız kadına ve kız çocuklarına yönelik şiddetin son bulması için dileklerini dilek yazdılar ve dilek ağacımıza astılar.

16 days of activism campaigne is continue at msyd-asra mamak community center.
our beneficiaries at mamak community center have made their wishes for violence against women and girls and wish them to hang on to our wish tree.

تستمر 16 يومًا من حملة النشاط في مركز msyd-asra  الاجتماعي ب mamak
وقد قامت المستفيدات لدينا في مركز مجتمع ماماك بتعليق رغباتهن في التصدي للعنف ضد النساء والفتيات  على شجرة الاماني ، ونتمنى لهن التمسك بشجرة رغباتنا.

text:
@speakerryan @nyt.fi @nyjah @nyrangers @nypl @nyknicks @nytcooking bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

she is brave!

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

aber das ist nicht das ende.

text:
how you handle your abuser is up to you.
there’s a lot of misinformation circling around about what survivors can and can’t do in the aftermath of narcissistic abuse.  as a grown adult, it’s up to you what you do.  or don’t do.  there are no set rules, as long as you don’t break the law.
.
.
.
many say you have to simply ignore what your abuser did to you, accept your fate and do nothing.
they say that “living well is the best revenge.”
but, not everyone wants revenge.  revenge against an emotionally immature, mentally ill non-person is petty and it’s focusing on the abuser.  some of us want justice.
.
.
.
getting #justice for myself  played a key part in my healing.  i went from being manipulated by the abuser to seeing him as the spineless little bitch he really is, in just a matter of weeks.  any lingering trauma bonding has been absolutely smashed to smithereens.  the only feelings i have left towards this individual are pity, and a degree of contempt.
.
.
.
as is typical with these passive-aggressive individuals, the narc made all kinds of pathetic threats.  he was going to sue me for refusing an abortion.  he was going to report me to the cops for posting about my abuse experiences on instagram.  he thought he could silence me by trying to project his own vile qualities onto me, in a series of illiterate, angry emails.  none of it worked.
i refused to listen to individuals who told me stuff like: “but it’s not your fault.  they are great manipulators.” or “it’s best not to cross them.  you don’t know what they are capable of.”
i took my power back by fighting back.
.
.
.

i’m not talking about engaging in direct arguments or any form of direct contact with this disturbed individual.  that would be an utter waste of time and energy.
i’m talking about changing the power dynamics. 
i let this pathetic excuse for a man know, in a variety of ways, that if he ever tries to cross me in any way, ever again, he’s finished.  completely #cancelled.  and the narcissist knows i’m not playing. and neither are my loved ones.  and neither is the judicial system, for that matter. .
.
.
continues in comments 👇👇👇
name: Life After Narc🌤
tweet_full:
how you handle your abuser is up to you.
there’s a lot of misinformation circling around about what survivors can and can’t do in the aftermath of narcissistic abuse.  as a grown adult, it’s up to you what you do.  or don’t do.  there are no set rules, as long as you don’t break the law.
.
.
.
many say you have to simply ignore what your abuser did to you, accept your fate and do nothing.
they say that “living well is the best revenge.”
but, not everyone wants revenge.  revenge against an emotionally immature, mentally ill non-person is petty and it’s focusing on the abuser.  some of us want justice.

text:
@huffposttaste @foxnews @nytimes bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
@huffposttaste @foxnews @nytimes in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
@huffposttaste @foxnews @nytimes in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian
