text:
@huffposttaste @foxnews @nytimes bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
dec 8 // a note she wrote on mint // celebrating 24 teas of christmas // our parents gave great parties and back then, the very best always led to three things – boney m being played till the amp exploded; slices of black forest cake flung against an exposed brick wall; and the detritus of a table including opened yet, uneaten boxes of red tulip after dinner mints. for two small girls, chocolate covered toothpaste was the equivalent of ecstasy. we were good at sneaking, my sister and i, and our hungover parents were good at sleeping and this combination found us tiptoeing down the shag pile, past their door, across the slate floor of the kitchen and round the corner to the billiards room, where our table converted into a dining space for twenty. it was here two small, forensic scientists would discover morning-after evidence of the night before. vinyl records strewn, cigarette ash, the aforementioned flung cherries and cream of ‘cake on the wall’ (years later we’d discover this was a game where instead of throwing knives, they threw cake, at an outstretched woman in her underwear – yep wtf – that was 1978 for you). and then, the wonder of it all - glamourous chocolates in tiny crinkly, black sleeves. it always amazed - how could grown-ups demonstrate such restraint as to leave such delight behind on the table? how could they not want to fill their pockets? and we’d fit as many as we could into our tiny hands before lying in humming silence on our backs under the table with our feet jammed up and we’d eat red tulips after dinner mints until we were practically sick. my record was 14. 
#tea2 #adventcalendar #christmas #tea #australia #afterdinnermints #love #sisters #1978 #party #empowerment #boneym #metoo #t2tea

text:
ieder jaar helpen we honderden kinderen en jongeren uit nederlanden die te maken hebben gehad met huiselijk geweld, verwaarlozing en uitbuiting. zij groeien vaak op in armoede of in situaties waarbij het vieren van een verjaardag, het volgen van zwemles, het dragen van een warme jas en het meedoen aan sociale activiteiten niet vanzelfsprekend is.⠀
⠀
we vragen je een donatie te doen en 4 mensen uit je omgeving te motiveren om dat ook te doen. als zij op hun beurt ook 4 mensen vragen te doneren en zij vervolgens hetzelfde doen, zorgen we samen voor een positieve toekomst voor deze kinderen. je kunt ook een eigen inzamelingsactie starten of je familieleden, vrienden en collega's vertellen over onze campagne.⠀

text:
no one remembers this bing crosby classic..it hasn't been banned..*(for entertainment purposes only*) .  #eazye #bingcrosby #bingcrosby #babyitscoldoutside #sensitive #hos #crooners #rappers #frankloessor #lynngarland  this #metoo-era-cum-yuletide-season, radio stations are pulling the plug on that holiday earworm with lyrics that, to some, ring date-rape warning bells, rather than evoking innocent snow-bound flirtation.

the tune "baby, it's cold outside," with words that seemed charming when fdr was in office, may land with a tone-deaf thud on the ear of today's listener.

text:
är du kåt?

text:
@speakerryan @burgerking_suomi @yleuutisluokka @maddowshow @arimelber @lastwordmsnbc @katyturnbc @stephruhle wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
elle | nog maar een paar dagen in de winkel: elle december met ons grote artikel over de expositie ‘femmes fatales’ in het @gemeentemuseum op pp. 82-85 💫 ✨ 💫⁣
⁣
wij interviewden conservator madelief hohé en art director maarten spruyt over de allereerste expositie ooit die volledig gewijd is aan vrouwelijke ontwerpers.⁣
⁣
“‘er is altijd veel maatschappelijk bewustzijn en activisme bij vrouwelijke ontwerpers geweest. denk bijvoorbeeld aan katharine hamnett die tijdens haar ontmoeting met de britse premier margaret thatcher in 1984 haar t-shirt met een protestleuze onthulde. hamnett sprak zich openlijk - door middel van mode - uit tegen thatchers beslissing om amerikaanse pershing-raketten te stationeren in groot-brittannië, ondanks dat 58% van de britten tegen had gestemd,’ vertelt hohé. tijdens de conceptfase van de expositie in het gemeentemuseum vonden ook de protestmarsen naar aanleiding van trumps eedaflegging plaats en kort daarna ontstond de #metoo-beweging. de tijd was rijp voor een tentoonstelling met alleen maar vrouwelijke makers: historische en hedendaagse vrouwen die met hun vernieuwende ontwerpen op de barricades staan voor waar ze in geloven.”⁣
⁣
verder lezen? @elle_nl december ligt nu in de winkel!⁣
⁣
🛍 ✨ 🛍 ✨ 🛍 ✨ 🛍 ✨ 🛍 ✨ 🛍 ⁣
⁣
⁣
📸: nr. 1: mary katrantzou, collectie zomer 2018. petrovsky & ramone (foto), maarten spruyt (art direction) voor gemeentemuseum den haag. courtesy mary katrantzou | nr. 2: stella mccartney. voorjaar 2017. petrovsky & ramone (foto), maarten spruyt (art direction) voor gemeentemuseum den haag. courtesy stella mccartney | nr. 3: drie avondjurken, callot soeurs (ca. 1920/24), chanel (1925), callot soeurs (ca. 1927). gemeentemuseum den haag | nr. 4: japonnen van zijde, tweede helft 18e eeuw, gemaakt door mannelijke kleermakers of vrouwelijke naaisters. gemeentemuseum den haag.⁣
⁣

西貢崇真天主教學校（小學部）爆30年前性侵醜聞

西貢崇真天主教學校(小學部)爆出爆性侵醜聞。多名女生報案，指控現任麥姓訓導主任當年非禮她們。警方接報後於今年初拘捕該涉案老師，經調查並徵詢律政司意見後，日前落案控告該名主任。而在校的家長及學生，竟全不知情，校方並無通知。 (門徒事工急需事奉人手，閱讀下文前，煩請先進入，登記您可以事奉的崗位，多謝合作！)
報案的數名30多歲的女士，是西貢崇真天主教學校(小學部)舊生。她們受「#metoo」事件啟發，於今年2月初報警，稱約於30年前在該校就讀小二及小三時，被時任英文科麥姓老師非禮。據悉在小息時，他召見女學生並摸裙底或撫摸私處等。警方接報調查後，確認至少有5名女受害人，於是在3月初拘捕該主任。校方道事件後，亦於同月暫停其職務，但並未對外公開他因非禮案而停職。他將被控告8項非禮罪，案件本月11日（二）於觀塘裁判法院提堂。

事件曝光後，一位居於英國的舊女生，向媒體透露自己就讀涉事小學時也曾被涉案教師非禮，創傷至今仍未能磨滅。她聲稱將會主動聯絡香港警方報案。

報案的數名30多歲的女士，是西貢崇真天主教學校(小學部)舊生。她們受「#metoo」事件啟發，於今年2月初報警，稱約於30年前在該校就讀小二及小三時，被時任英文科麥姓老師非禮。據悉在小息時，他召見女學生並摸裙底或撫摸私處等。警方接報調查後，確認至少有5名女受害人，於是在3月初拘捕該主任。校方道事件後，亦於同月暫停其職務，但並未對外公開他因非禮案而停職。他將被控告8項非禮罪，案件本月11日（二）於觀塘裁判法院提堂。

事件曝光後，一位居於英國的舊女生，向媒體透露自己就讀涉事小學時也曾被涉案教師非禮，創傷至今仍未能磨滅。她聲稱將會主動聯絡香港警方報案。

text:
"i was so young and much in demand. yet it was always difficult for me to price myself in terms of the services i offered. i came up with a plan to make it easier for me i asked a veteran prostituted woman who was a roommate of mine to put up the prices and she did.

from the onset the rules that i set were not being adhered to by these many men i encountered. it really depended on the money and the fantasy they had and most times they would change from the initial agreement and did as they pleased.

my first violation would be when someone would ask me “uthengisa ngamalini ? “– meaning how much are you selling for?

my heart would throb as i couldn’t give selling my soul to the devil a price and that price would be so disgraceful with my street experience i guarantee that there’s no amount of money that can compensate one for sexual intercourse with unknown males." read more: http://embracedignity.org.za/zenande-story-prostitution-is-violence-against-women/

the marvelous mrs. maisel is back! if anyone needs me i’ll be at the gaslight café all weekend, smoking cigarettes and busting up.
.
“we’re having these very important moments and talking about things, and hopefully stripping away stigmas—sexual harassment and assault, the mistreatment of women, and the micro and macro violence that women have experienced in this world,” brosnahan observed of #metoo and #timesup. “this is a movement that was started by women long, long ago.”
.
whether midge realizes it or not, she is a part of that movement just by virtue of being a woman trying to be a stand-up comedian. golden globe winner brosnahan said that as soon as she read the “mrs. maisel” script she knew “midge was a woman with an unshakeable and constant sense of self-empowerment,” even if the character wouldn’t self-identify as a feminist. - #womeninhollywood

text:
🎗️수요일, 아산병원 장례식장으로 김순옥 할머니의 조문을 다녀온 이후, 마음이 너무 무거웠다. 그래서 오늘 전주에 와서 첫 일정으로 [평화의소녀상]에 왔다. 이 곳에 챙겨간 보라색리본을 걸어두며 빈의자에 앉았다.
.
🎗️평화의 소녀상은 일본군 성노예 할머니들을 상징하는 조형물이자, 일제의 만행을 고발하는 의미이며, 다시는 나라를 빼앗기지 않겠다는 민족적 결의를 담은 우리들의 양심이라고 한다.
.
🎗️내가 앉은 빈 의자는 세가지 의미가 있다고 한다. 하나는 먼저 세상을 떠난 할머니들의 빈자리이며, 두번째는 소녀상을 찾는 이들의 자리이며, 마지막은 평화, 인권, 그리고 진실을 위해 끝까지 싸워온 할머니들의 염원을 미래세대가 이어받아 끝까지 함께 하겠다는 약속의 의미다.
.
🎗️페미니즘을 실천하는 방법은 그다지 멀리 있지도, 어렵지도 않다. 일상에서 작은 것 하나씩 실천하면 된다. 앞으로 나는 미래세대로서 책임감을 가지고 위안부문제해결과 평화를 위해 노력할 것이며, 마지막으로 고개숙여 김순옥 할머니의 명복을 빈다.
name: 박은수 EunSoo Park 朴恩秀

stop_filter_tweet: 🎗️수요일 , 아산병원 장례식장으로 김순옥 할머니의 조문을 다녀온 이후 , 마음이 너무 무거웠다 . 그래서 오늘 전주에 와서 첫 일정으로 [ 평화의소녀상 ] 에 왔다 . 이 곳에 챙겨간 보라색리본을 걸어두며 빈의자에 앉았다 . . 🎗️평화의 소녀상은 일본군 성노예 할머니들을 상징하는 조형물이자 , 일제의 만행을 고발하는 의미이며 , 다시는 나라를 빼앗기지 않겠다는 민족적 결의를 담은 우리들의 양심이라고 한다 . . 🎗️내가 앉은 빈 의자는 세가지 의미가 있다고 한다 . 하나는 먼저 세상을 떠난 할머니들의 빈자리이며 , 두번째는 소녀상을 찾는 이들의 자리이며 , 마지막은 평화 , 인권 , 그리고 진실을 위해 끝까지 싸워온 할머니들의 염원을 미래세대가 이어받아 끝까지 함께 하겠다는 약속의 의미다 . . 🎗️페미니즘을 실천하는 방법은 그다지 멀리 있지도 , 어렵지도 않다 . 일상에서 작은 것 하나씩 실천하면 된다 . 앞으로 나는 미래세대로서 책임감을 가지고 위안부문제해결과 평화를 위해 노력할 것이며 , 마지막으로 고개숙여 김순옥 할머니의 명복을 빈다 .

“eggshell skull: a legal doctrine that a defendant must ‘take their victim as they find them’. if a single punch kills someone because of their thin skull, that victim’s weakness cannot mitigate the seriousness of the crime.”
but what if your ‘victim’ is a strong, determined accuser who knows the legal system and won’t back down until justice is done? .
.
.

.
.
.

text:
30 ноября 2018 года, в 15:00, в главном корпусе государственного медицинского университета былай проведена акция «16 дней активных действий против гендерного насилия», организованной агентствами организации объединенных наций совместно с оюл “национальная волонтерская сеть” и волонтерским корпусом государственного медицинского университета города семей.
акция направлена на то, чтобы привлечь внимание общественности к проблеме насилия, изменить стереотипы отношений и поведения, существующие в обществе, покончить с глобальным распространением насилия в отношении женщин и девочек.
в рамках акции в 17 региональных центрах казахстана при поддержке гражданского сектора, местных властей и образовательных учреждений пройдут флешмобы и дискуссионные сессии в формате интерактивного театра на тему насилия, дискриминации, и гендерных предрассудков под названием #услышьтеменя: искореним насилие в отношении женщин (#hearmetoo: end violence against women). за последний год движения #metoo, #немолчи, #timesup и многие другие вызвали волну дискуссий в обществе по всему миру на тему насилия, дискриминации, сексуальных домогательств в отношении женщин. при этом, на каждый случай, получивший широкий общественный резонанс и внимание сми, приходятся тысячи женщин по всему миру, которые ведут ежедневную борьбу против гендерной дискриминации и насилия. таким образом, тема #услышьтеменя: искореним насилие в отношении женщин – это также призыв усилить голоса активистов и правозащитников, выслушать тех, кто пережил насилие, положить конец культуре замалчивания в нашем обществе и объединится во благо женщин и девочек.
“насилие против женщин и девочек – это глобальная пандемия. это унижение для всех женщин и девочек, это клеймо для каждого общества, это огромная преграда для инклюзивного, справедливого и устойчивого развития. по сути своей насилие в отношении женщин и девочек есть свидетельство глубокого неуважения - неумения мужчин признать неотъемлемое право женщин на равенство, уважать их достоинство. это вопрос обеспечения основополагающих прав человека», - отметил генеральный секретарь оон антониу гутерриш в своем послании по случаю международного дня борьбы за ликвидацию насилия.
name: QazMed Volunteers
tweet_full:
30 ноября 2018 года, в 15:00, в главном корпусе государственного медицинского университета былай проведена акция «16 дней активных действий против гендерного насилия», организованной агентствами организации объединенных наций совместно с оюл “национальная волонтерская сеть” и волонтерским корпусом государственного медицинского университета города семей.
акция направлена на то, чтобы привлечь внимание общественности к проблеме насилия, изменить стереотипы отношений и поведения, существующие в обществе, покончить с глобальным распространением насилия в отношении женщин и девочек.
в рамках акции в 17 региональных центрах казахстана при поддержке гражданского сектора, местных властей и образовательных учреждений пройдут флешмобы и дискуссионные сессии в формате интерактивного театра на тему насилия, дискриминации, и гендерных предрассудков под названием #услышьтеменя: искореним насилие в отношении женщин (#hearmetoo: end violence against women). за последний год движения #metoo, #немолчи, #timesup и многие другие вызвали волну дискуссий в обществе по всему миру на тему насилия, дискриминации, сексуальных домогательств в отношении женщин. при этом, на каждый случай, получивший широкий общественный резонанс и внимание сми, приходятся тысячи женщин по всему миру, которые ведут ежедневную борьбу против гендерной дискриминации и насилия. таким образом, тема #услышьтеменя: искореним насилие в отношении женщин – это также призыв усилить голоса активистов и правозащитников, выслушать тех, кто пережил насилие, положить конец культуре замалчивания в нашем обществе и объединится во благо женщин и девочек.
“насилие против женщин и девочек – это глобальная пандемия. это унижение для всех женщин и девочек, это клеймо для каждого общества, это огромная преграда для инклюзивного, справедливого и устойчивого развития. по сути своей насилие в отношении женщин и девочек есть свидетельство глубокого неуважения - неумения мужчин признать неотъемлемое право женщин на равенство, уважать их достоинство. это вопрос обеспечения основополагающих прав человека», - отметил генеральный секретарь оон антониу гутерриш в своем послании по случаю международного дня борьбы за ликвидацию насилия.

stop_filter_tweet: 30 ноября 2018 года , в 15:00 , в главном корпусе государственного медицинского университета былай проведена акция « 16 дней активных действий против гендерного насилия » , организованной агентствами организации объединенных наций совместно с оюл “ национальная волонтерская сеть ” и волонтерским корпусом государственного медицинского университета города семей . акция направлена на то , чтобы привлечь внимание общественности к проблеме насилия , изменить стереотипы отношений и поведения , существующие в обществе , покончить с глобальным распространением насилия в отношении женщин и девочек . в рамках акции в 17 региональных центрах казахстана при поддержке гражданского сектора , местных властей и образовательных учреждений пройдут флешмобы и дискуссионные сессии в формате интерактивного театра на тему насилия , дискриминации , и гендерных предрассудков под названием искореним насилие в отношении женщин ( end violence women ) . за последний год движения и многие другие вызвали волну дискуссий в обществе по всему миру на тему насилия , дискриминации , сексуальных домогательств в отношении женщин . при этом , на каждый случай , получивший широкий общественный резонанс и внимание сми , приходятся тысячи женщин по всему миру , которые ведут ежедневную борьбу против гендерной дискриминации и насилия . таким образом , тема искореним насилие в отношении женщин – это также призыв усилить голоса активистов и правозащитников , выслушать тех , кто пережил насилие , положить конец культуре замалчивания в нашем обществе и объединится во благо женщин и девочек . “ насилие против женщин и девочек – это глобальная пандемия . это унижение для всех женщин и девочек , это клеймо для каждого общества , это огромная преграда для инклюзивного , справедливого и устойчивого развития . по сути своей насилие в отношении женщин и девочек есть свидетельство глубокого неуважения - неумения мужчин признать неотъемлемое право женщин на равенство , уважать их достоинство . это вопрос обеспечения основополагающих прав человека » , - отметил генеральный секретарь оон антониу гутерриш в своем послании по случаю международного дня борьбы за ликвидацию насилия .

text:
i am humbled to be able to lead an organization that has such a profound impact on our direct community. jida@refugeelink.com  for more ways to be a part of the change ************************************ ***🇺🇸 dear supporters,
on behalf of the amaanah board, i am pleased to announce that jida nabulsi will be joining amaanah refugee services’ team as the chief executive officer. her leadership will be effective december 10th, 2018. 
jida joins us with over a decade of strategic marketing experience in the oil and gas industry, most recently as a senior analyst at exterran in houston. there, she was forecasting trends, managing budgetary tasks, and spearheading company-wide goals and initiatives. 
her decision to leave the corporate world was driven by her passion to lead a community service organization and serve resettled refugees. as a hands-on supporter for over nine years and developer of our signature pink & blue refugee family event, jida will be a great fit as we continue to uphold our promise to the resettled refugee community.

she brings with her the organizational skills, strategy development and company branding experience that will confidently pave a path forward in strengthening our mission to integrate resettled refugees into their new homes and communities. 
jida has a bachelor’s degree in finance and economics from the university of st. thomas and is certified in marketing strategy from cornell university. she is currently pursuing an mba from texas a&m university. 
as we turn the page from our 10-year anniversary, we are very excited to welcome jida as our new ceo.

sincerely,

roger yelton

chairman of the board

text:
@regran_ed from @queenofpettysjt -  @regran_ed from @unheardvoicesmag -  a woman who was 16 when she killed a #nashville man who solicited her for sex must serve at least 51 years in prison before she’s eligible for release, according to the #tennessee supreme court.

on thursday the court said defendants like #cyntoiabrown , who are convicted of first-degree murder committed after july 1, 1995 and sentenced to life imprisonment, can’t become eligible for release from prison before serving more than five decades.

thursday’s ruling came in response to a lawsuit in which brown argues her sentence is unconstitutional, citing a 2012 opinion by the us supreme court that said mandatory life sentences without parole for juvenile offenders violate the us constitution.

the #tennesseesupremecourt explained in a statement that “under state law, a life sentence is a determinate sentence of 60 years. however, the sixty-year sentence can be reduced by up to 15 percent, or 9 years, by earning various sentence credits.” a district court previously denied brown’s motion, per court documents, pointing out she hadn’t been sentenced to life in prison without the possibility of parole — just a life sentence.

the case is pending judgment by the sixth circuit court of appeals, which asked the tennessee supreme court to share its opinion.

more than a decade after sentencing, brown’s case caught the attention of a-list celebrities like #rihanna and #kimkardashianwest who began advocating for mercy. her story spread on social media using the hashtag #freecyntoiabrown 
brown says she was forced into prostitution after a difficult childhood. at her trial, she said her victim, #johnnymitchellallan , solicited her for sex and drove her to his house.

there, brown saw a gun cabinet in allan’s room, she said during her trial. she resisted him until he appeared to reach under the bed, at which point she believed he was going to kill her. brown took a gun out of her purse and shot allan, killing him.

in a clemency hearing in may, the tennessee board of parole was split on its recommendation to gov. bill haslam. two of the six member voted to grant clemency, two to deny it, and two to make

text:
i am not
self
made
i am made by bowed heads and bloody knees 
chained hands and thrashed backs
bruises and love, pain and sacrifice on my behalf
i am hands lifting and pulling me
a village surrounding me
a tribe fighting for me
a god protecting me, forgiving me, keeping me
nay sayers, cheerleaders, champions and weapons drawn against me
i am made by the constant fight for black skinned justice
the screams of pain from me too ‘cause #metoo
lessons from classrooms with hands raised and guns so violent even with... hands raised
all the pain made me, laughter made me, my mama made me, my husband made me, my sons made me, my teachers made me, my sisters made me
i was made with a pen in my hand, gun in my hand fighting for  someone else’s land 
i am bold, brilliant, successful and proud. i am humble, grateful and blessed. i am all these things and more things but i didn’t make me. i’m so many people, places and things within me. with a god tied bow around me. 
i am not
self

text:
december 7, 1941. on that day in history, 2,403 american lives were lost. to most people this is a number. but each and every single one of those numbers; 1 through 2,403, was an individual life, an individual spirit. and each of those lost lives affected hundreds of others. as humans, we naturally go about day to day, with expectations and assumptions of what will happen. in other words, we don’t expect the unexpected. because of this, many people don’t truly think about how thankful they are for those around them. we don’t truly understand how grateful we are for someone until we’ve lost them. the families, friends, and loved ones that lost those that mattered most to them on that fateful day, likely woke up with the expectation that they would see them. but life does not follow a pattern, nor does it meet expectations. men and women of great spirit were lost on this day, so long ago. but we rose up as a nation and as one people. 4 years later, japan wished they had never touched foot on american soil. when we come together as one nation, and as one people, we can do great things. when we are thankful, even for those that seem like our enemies, we become stronger than the fear or hate that separates is. so when you wake up in the morning, be thankful, even for the people that may not be thankful for you. when you love your enemy as yourself, great things can be accomplished and great men and women can rise up. this is america.

text: most know... i am very open about my sexual assault. tonight i took a huge step and sent him a letter. but i was scared, more so than i thought was possible... i mean, this was 15 years ago and i truly thought i had most of my emotions secure when it came to this. but i realized that talking about it factually and actually feeling it while talking about it emotionally are two very... very different things. it took me awhile to send it because i kept having major panic attacks. this was my reaction right before sending it, but i did it... and i got my voice. he finally gets to hear what i couldn't say as a child and now... i feel calm. #rapesurvivor #survivors #assault #metoo

text:
тарана бёрк — лицо движения против сексуальных домогательств

для вас, тупые шовинистические мужские свиньи, поясняем: хэштег #metoo, афтаром которого является данная афро–американская девушка, какбэ символизирует и означает "меня тоже сексуально домогались!" и призывает к солидарности всех жертв сексуального насилия.

тарана берк начала движение «me too» более десяти лет назад и наблюдала, как хэштег стал сплачивающим кличем после харви вайнштейна.

text:
from @gshrudayana -  the mirror never lies adalah film fiksi arahan kamila andini pada tahun 2011. tahun ini datang kesempatan untuk kita menontonnya bersama sama!

hari: sabtu, 8 desember 2018
jam: registrasi dibuka mulai pukul 16.00 wita 
venue: lantai 2 warung @menbrayut
.
"clothes aren't going to change the world. the women who wear them will."
.
ada keterkaitan antara ruang hidupmu (lingkungan) dengan kehidupan juga penghidupan. fashion, baik baju maupun perhiasan adalah industri penghasil limbah yang besar bagi lingkungan. myra juliarti (desainer @akusiji) dan dian suri (desainer @kunangjewelry) memiliki kesamaan semangat dalam mengawali bisnisnya agar bertanggung jawab bagi lingkungan dan sosial.

ada cerita apa saja dari mereka? bagaimana tantangan yang ada dan apakah ada harapan terwujudnya revolusi fashion di masa kini?

dengarkan semuanya di #hearmetoo session setelah pemutaran. yuk berakhir pekan bersama enam belas film festival bali!

festival ini gratis dengan komitmen zerowaste, jadi bawa tumbler/botol minumnya ya!

text:
how to ask your boss for a mental health day:
plante suggests being as specific as possible when you ask. we often refer to our mental struggles in vague terms because we don’t want to disclose too much in the workplace, but perhaps if your boss knew you were using the afternoon to recharge in the outdoors or go to a therapy appointment, she could become less skeptical of what the day actually means to you. also, work on phrasing the request to let your manager know that you’re taking this time so you can come back mentally stronger, refreshed, and in a better place to be productive at work.

that being said, “mental health days can help in the short term, but they might not help in the long term if there’s a bigger problem to be addressed,” plante says. “a day off can help, but it also might be indicative of a larger issue,” he says, and if you suspect that’s the case, it’s better to consult with a therapist.

text: i’ve been on a “spiritual path” since before i left my parents fundamentalist religion. i’ve been to workshops and talks and youtube’s and books and healers and teachers...i’ve done almost everything. but the truth is, you gotta find your wound. the big one or ones. even if you’re not angry you were molested at 5, or raped at 13. even if your narcissistic dead mother can’t hurt you from her grave or whatever version of pain you endured is, you must find your trauma. it lives in your cells. it lives under your words and lines your aura. it’s in your handshakes and behind your smile and in the outside corners of your eyes. it coats the life you are building and maintaining and cleaning and rebuilding and demolishing and rebuilding...find your trauma. feel that shit. let it out. it’s the only thing that’ll work. it’s the only key. #theonlywaytoitisthroughit #trauma #healing #shame #metoo #narcissisticabuse #itainteasybutigotthis #askforhelp #ifnotnowwhen #cleansacredsmall #witchythings

text:
ahhhhhh! this soup! it’s my go to comfort dinner when it’s cold outside and it has been cold here in dallas.
.
this soup is also easy, fast (start to finish is 30 min), and delicious. seriously, i have yet to meet anyone who doesn’t love this soup! #asoulsurvivormeals
.
here’s the other thing about this soup, it has no name! i told my husband i wanted to call it carrot chowder and he was like 🤢. he then suggested halloween soup since we always have it for dinner on halloween but i didn’t love that. so we have yet to find a name for it! 😂😂 if you have any awesome ideas leave them in the comments section!
.
please ... do not be scared away by the carrots in this soup. i am 100% serious when i say everyone likes this soup! .
- 1lb lean ground beef (93/7)
- 4 cups tomato juice
- 2 cans cream of celery
- 1 1/2 cups water
- 1 tsp garlic salt
- 1 tsp pepper
- 2 cups shredded carrots. i buy large carrots and shred them but you can buy the pre shredded carrots if you’d rather. .
1. in a large pot brown hamburger over medium heat and drain.
2. all all other ingredients and stir to combine.
3. turn heat up to high and allow soup to come to a boil.
4. reduce heat to low/medium and let simmer for 20 minutes making sure to stir occasionally. serves 6. cal: 224 c: 17.9 f: 7.9 p: 18.3

text:
“even when it’s not pretty or perfect. even when it’s more real than you want it to be. your story is what you have, what you will always have. it is something to own.“- @michelleobama
.....
.....
so here is part of my story. it’s not pretty and it’s sometimes too real, but it’s mine. i was humbled, scared, and excited when @jendeanphoto asked me to share my story on her podcast, the gardenia project (it’s recently made the @mainepublic short list of podcasts!). it’s a storytelling podcast with portraits of strong women to show that we are resilient, and that there is usually more to anyone than what is seen on the outside. in the newest episode, i share a story that i’ve kept hidden for years, but am beginning to share more and more because it is a part of me. it is intense; and i feel humbled, scared and excited again today. it’s not something i’d typically share with my clients, but i’m sharing in hopes of showing that we can heal and be whole no matter what happens. light is always more powerful than darkness. ....
....
there is a trigger warning for those with sexual assault pasts, but i will say that there are not many details. we focused on the healing journey rather than the trauma. ....
....
link in bio or listen on itunes by searching “the gardenia project.” also @jendeanphoto is magical. like really magical. ...
...

text:
i've *been* saying this for years! have you listened to the lyrics of the holiday song 'baby it's cold outside'? 😒  it's a whole entire assault! 🤦🏾‍♀️
.
p.s. i posted this on fb & yt yesterday and folks been done lost their whole entireminds. 😐 who knew folks were that serious about their suggestive holiday songs. 🤔 🤷🏾‍♀️ yes i know the context was different in the 1940s, yes i know it's a husband and wife that used to sing the song, yes i know there are other songs with worse lyrics, yes i know 'what's in this drink' was a running joke, no it has nothing to do with bill cosby or the #metoo movement. i've always thought this. i said what i said. 🙃 be best. ✌🏾
🚶🏾‍♀️ #glamazinivideo

text:
einmal #fordinant #waschen . vor der #arbeit bin ich kurz mit unserem auto waschen gefahren.  dabei genüsslich kaffee getrunken ☕😊 nach der tour nach hause und um 8 uhr klingelt wieder der wecker 🙄🤨 lkw reparieren vom kollegen. wieder mal ein tolles wochenende 😔 es fällt leider immer was an. ich sehne mich nach meinem urlaub in 2 wochen, glaubt mir, ich werde alles ausschalten was geht um mich einfach auszuruhen und mich um meine #familie zu kümmern. mometan haben wir als #family wenig zeit zusammen leider 😔 hoffe es geht nachher schnell das lackieren und anbauen. spätestens um 13 uhr will ich wieder zu hause sein. sonntag planen wir vielleicht mal was tolles. mal sehen wie das wetter wird. ich werde mir mal was überlegen für meine liebsten ❤. euch ein schönes #wochenende .
.....

when i was 15, a this guy jerked off next to me on the bus while i was on my way home from secondary school. he still had the audacity to ask me for tissue paper.
.
when i was 18, this guy pressed up against me with his hard on in a crowded train.
.
when i was 20 on christmas eve, a guy followed me through the car park and blocks (trust me, i didn’t realize he was actually following me at that point) and finally into the lift. he lifted up my dress and touched my bum as i was exiting the lift towards my own home. i experienced this terror for the next 5 years entering lifts with strangers.
.
you think singapore’s safe? singapore is only safe when we stop this stupid culture of slut shaming, this culture of guys thinking it’s ok to touch women without their permission & this stupid culture of cyber bullying and sexually harassing women online. #metoo
.
women should have the freedom to move their bodies how they want to.
.
join @elvinac & @freedomyogasg on their campaign #whyhidegowide to end this nonsense.

text:
meeting the dalai lama with nkt survivors (part 4)

by erika adler (continued from part 3)........it was time for our meeting to end, but hh seemed unwilling to leave us. he told carol that she and jeremy, one of his aides, should talk about meeting up again in dharamsala. he invited us all to visit him there and told us he would remember us. he shook our hands again, embraced people, and pulled us all together for a group photograph, something i will always remember.

i had heard a great deal about the nkt from carol and other survivors, and seen footage of their noisy protests against hh, but until i was the o2 arena on saturday i’d never seen them face to face. it felt disgusting, in the same way that visiting a broken toilet is disgusting. i knew it was going to stink, and it did.

but our meeting with the dalai lama has left an enduring impression on me of hope. it was incredibly reassuring to hear him tell us to go back to the original teachings of the buddha, which in my experience can so easily get lost under the many traditions and practices that are taught in the west. i don’t know (yet) what others are feeling, but it now feels entirely possible that his effect on all of us will create ripples yet to be imagined... erika

did you hear hannah gadsby’s speach given yesterday at the hollywood reporter’s 2018 women in entertainment gala? she discussed the irritating habit “good men” have of discussing “bad men”. this is an issue close to our hearts and speaks to the deep set attitudes and beliefs of men and women about the role we all play. 
do yourself a favour and look up her speech. she raises some really interesting points.
hannah gadsby is an australian comedian who has been well known to australian audiences since 2006 but she shot to international fame with the release of her netflix stand up special nanette. she is an outspoken advocate of equality and inclusion.

text: if you have ever wondered about why the#metoo movement is important. if you have ever wondered why or how someone could be a serial abuser. if you have ever questioned a victim's story or found yourself rationalizing behavior that borders on abuse.... listen to the podcast series believed. it is not for the faint of heart and many moments are hard to listen to. but it is so important to hear and understand what happened in the case of larry nassar. it's important to know that there are times when we need to critically think about implicit trust, to know when to question what we know to be true, and to talk about things that seem wrong or out of place. hundreds of girls were abused because most didn't understand or didn't think they would be believed or spoke up and were shut down. but when the story was out and they knew they weren't alone, it all changed. they were validated. || abuse (sexual, emotional, physical, verbal) doesn't happen in a vacuum. it happens within the context of relationship, trust, and believing what we know to be true. an abuser's greatest protection is in causing their victim to question whether or not something is actually wrong and/or that they will be believed if they say anything. || let's strive to ask the right questions, listen for the answers, and critically approach the status quo. let's strive to see what we don't want to believe is true.... for the sake of ourselves and the generations to come.

text: nothing inspires me more than meeting women who see the world without limits. meet crystal. she started present plate; a community organization that brings people together to learn the story behind the plate and re-wire our relationships to food. her two-gal team hosts knowledge-sharing dinners where chefs, farmers and guests foster new ways of thinking about food. oh did i mention she has a full-time job? yeah this is just her side-hustle. despite her full plate (😉), she exudes a sense of ease and calm that makes me realize, when you fill your life with intention and purpose, it doesn’t feel like work.

text:
so for those who don't know, this has been a long time coming for me to post this officially. but a month or two ago, i wrote and submitted a poem for the possibility to be included in an anthology that talks about sexual harassment and sexual assault. i received an email from indie blu(e) who told me my poem was accepted to be included in the anthology. 
well, on december 1st, we will not be silenced: the lived experience of sexual harassment and sexual assault told powerfully through poetry, prose, essay, and art was published! i of course have already ordered and received a copy for myself and have taken some pictures of me, the anthology and some of my poem. i can't be any happier about this whole thing and have written a blog post about it, which can be seen here:  https://rainyday.blog/2018/12/07/why-we-will-not-be-silenced-the-lived-experience-of-sexual-harassment-and-sexual-assault-told-powerfully-through-poetry-prose-essay-and-art-is-important-to-me/

thank you everyone for being so supportive of me and my writing endeavors! please get the book if you can because proceeds go to sexual harassment and sexual assault survivors. #blog #post #important #wewillnotbesilenced #metoo #poetry #sexualharassment #sexualassault
